               photosynthesis, proportional to CO2 uptake and water loss
               through plant stomata. SIF provides a high-resolution snapshot
               of the ``side door,'' scaling with the light captured by leaves.
               These two independent pieces of information help us understand
               plant water and carbon exchange. A coordinated effort to
               generate SIF and OCS data through satellite, airborne, and
               ground observations will improve our process-based models to
               predict how these cycles will change in the future.",
  journal   = "Bull. Am. Meteorol. Soc.",
