               productivity, which highlights the importance of accounting for
               variations in atmospheric COS mole fractions. The change to a
               different soil model, on the other hand, had a relatively small
               effect on the global biosphere COS sink. The small role of the
               modeled soil component in the COS budget supports the use of COS
               as a global photosynthesis tracer.",
